I decided to use it purely due to an advertisment for ORG187 fuel, I'm autistic so I follow what's Infront of me and expect what I read to be as simple as what I read.  It stated ¬£20 fuel voucher when you buy insurance, OK - I bought insurance and after a while no email or details.  My P.A (who helps me with decisions and dealing with companies) asked me if I received the voucher, I went and looked and only after pressing 'read more' did it open up a step by step.  If this had been clear and not hidden, I would have redeemed it.. not to mention you need an account to purchase insurance through this company so verification could and should be immediate upon a successful purchase, the company clearly knows this is a mistake people will make in order to legally avoid providing something offered to sweeten a deal.  On top of this the information they provide on the insurers is terrible, for the company I went with there was a lot of hidden fees regarding changes and cancellations charged not just by the broker, but both companies... this information is only provided AFTER purchasing the insurance.  I've never posted a review before, but I feel this company exploited my disability in order to sell me a low quality service and lured me in on a dishonest redemption policy.  I realise people who can be forward and confrontational/confident with companies can have much better experiences, but I hope anyone reading this can realise others don't have this ability, and get exploited regularly in different ways by companies like confused.  Worst part was when they refused me, they're still actually running the promotion as of the date I posted this.

Do not trust the insurance companies they provide.   QA Choice Insurance/ XS Direct: This company has caused me nothing but trouble and put me in the worst financial difficulty. I was a named driver on a car i got through my work for my mum. I had a seriously bad accident in the vehicle and it got written off. I made a claim and the company took 3 weeks to make a decision to void the insurance due to the V5 being in my name (the named driver) instead of my mums name (the main driver). This was an unintentional accident made when setting up the insurance and the company were not interest in the trouble this had caused us at all. Rude staff and no understanding for their customers. The company then changed us £300 to cancel the account as they voided the insurance, £1500 for storage of the vehicle when they had taken 3 weeks to make the decision to void and £1200 for the inspector who came to my house to interview myself and mum after the incident. The company refused to give us back our £3800 premium and yet still charged us £3000 charges. This has left us in £24,000 debt and a void on our insurance policy. This company will do everything in its power to not support their customers and get out of paying any claim. AVOID AT ALL TIMES!

In few words a FRAUD. That is a example that you found in the contract:  “If you decide to cancel your insurance policy outside of the cooling off period, the insurer will reclaim a proportion of commission back from us. We will apply a fee equivalent to that amount and deduct it from any returned premium from the insurer, or add it to any outstanding balance due on your premium finance.”  This is what I signed and unfortunately I will be pay. Read carefully before signing.

These guys misled me into funding my account. I received no less than three emails informing (and congratulating) me that my account application had been 'approved'. On that basis, I transferred a not insignificant sum. The problems started when I went to make my first trade, but received an error message saying that my residential address was still being verified. Surely, if my account was 'approved', that meant that all checks were complete and my account was ready to use? Apparently not with IB! I would not have funded the account had I not been led to think that everything was good to go.   So, on to the customer support, which is really, really, really, slow and unhelpful. After an hour-long live chat with excruciating waits in between responses, I was told that someone would be contacting me by email soon to help me get it resolved ASAP. I accepted that, but, still annoyed, filed my own complaint ticket as well. 24 hours later, I had received neither an email from an IB representative (aside from another generic one reminding me that my account was now 'approved' and funded!), nor a response to my complaint ticket.   Having lost faith in IB and wanting to take my business elsewhere, I tried to withdraw my funds and close my account, only to be told that I must wait three days before I can do so. Well this new nhs repeat prescription service online is a step in the right direction, but with so many flaws!  First, it’s is difficult switching between multiple people (I order for my whole family, 4 people). This is dangerous because items can unintentionally be ordered for the wrong person. I am careful so this is unlikely, but the potential is there. To switch, you have to click ORG64 logo, but this isn’t obvious at all!!  There is no option to change email address, you have to deactivate and start again, losing patient history of ordered meds.  There is no option to add medication on standby in bag to order at a later date. I am just trying to set it up for my family (don’t need ordering now, but later) so now I have to wait to add med details in until it is time to order instead of it being pre-populated.   There is no updates as advertised (request sent to gp, approved by gp, packing meds etc). The only notification I got was order received and order ready to collect. And can’t view this on the service online.  Also when ordering once set up, you have to go through all the details again. Why isn’t there a function to remember basic details like gp practice, chosen pharmacy of collection, exemption status etc. This drags out the process for each person. This is important to add in, there should just be an option to change details if needed.   Otherwise, app looks sleek and again a step in the right direction. Please fix the above flaws that stick out like a sore thumb!!
